public class KmlDateTime
extends KmlObjectPartial

Represents a specific point in time. The plugin accepts time in this format only; it does not accept JavaScript date or time objects.

Method Detail

get

public final java.lang.String get()
Returns:
Returns the date and time in XML Schema time format.

set

public final void set(java.lang.String date)
Set the date. Accepts only XML Schema time (see XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#isoformats). The value can be expressed as yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sszzzzzz, where T is the separator between the date and the time, and the time zone is either Z(for UTC) or zzzzzz, which represents +/-hh:mm in relation to UTC. Additionally, the value can be expressed as a date only.

Parameters:
date - the date. Accepts only XML Schema time (see XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#isoformats). The value can be expressed as yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sszzzzzz, where T is the separator between the date and the time, and the time zone is either Z(for UTC) or zzzzzz, which represents +/-hh:mm in relation to UTC. Additionally, the value can be expressed as a date only.
